        "header": "1Introduction",
        "images": [
            {
                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2605.15012/2605.15012v1/x1.png",
                "caption": "Figure 1:Overview of our work. We introduce a few-shot demonstration-guided RLVR paradigm to address three primary challenges: the lack of on-demand data, limited expert input, and high overfitting risk. To mitigate, FEST incorporates three vital components—supervised learning,on-policy learning, anddecaying weight—to effectively leverage few-shot data. Specifically, FEST jointly optimizes the model using GRPO on the answer-only data (DID_{I}) and a semi-online DPO loss on the few-shot SFT data (DED_{E}). The latter utilizes adaptiveβ\\betacoefficients to weight different types of rollouts, bridging the gap between expert demonstrations (y+y^{+}) and agent-generated samples (y−y^{-}).",
                "position": 254
            }
        ]
